# Push Frontend to GitHub

After completing frontend work in this project, commit and push to the `blackrock` remote unless the user explicitly says not to.

## Remote

- **Remote name:** `blackrock`
- **Repository:** https://github.com/owiekelvin3-cpu/Blackrock-reserve.git
- **Branch:** `main` (tracks `blackrock/main`)

## Include (frontend)

- Marketing pages: `src/app/(marketing)/`, `src/app/(auth)/`
- Customer dashboard UI: `src/components/dashboard/`, `src/components/auth/`, `src/components/layout/`, `src/components/marketing/`, `src/components/chat/`, `src/components/ui/`
- User-facing API routes (not admin): `src/app/api/` except `src/app/api/admin/`
- Shared libs used by the public site: `src/lib/chatbot.ts`, `src/lib/email*.ts`, `src/lib/env.ts`, `src/lib/site-url.ts`, etc.
- Styles/assets: `src/app/globals.css`, `public/`, `tailwind.config.ts`
- Project config/docs: `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `README.md`, `DEPLOYMENT.md`, `.env.example`

## Exclude (admin / local-only)

- `src/app/admin/`
- `src/app/api/admin/`
- `src/components/admin/`
- `scripts/`
- Admin-only libs: `src/lib/admin-*.ts`, `src/lib/balance-adjustment.ts`, `src/lib/query-batch.ts`
- `src/hooks/use-admin-fetch.ts`

## Workflow

1. Stage only frontend paths (never `git add .` blindly).
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push: `git push blackrock main`
4. Do not push to `origin` unless the user asks.
5. Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
